snippet.textDisplay:
Can you please do a video on styling patchy hair? I just had a baby and (like a lot of women) had about 1/3 of my hair fall out due to postpartum hormones.

Most of the hair that came out is right at my natural part so I look like I have a mini-mullet now that the hair is starting to grow back. I already know to take vitamins to help the hair grow back healthy but I have no clue how to style it so I don't look stupid or damage the new growth.

I'm scared to gel the short new growth down cuz I don't want the hair breaking. I already had a little bit of tension alopecia at the hairline and I have fine hair that's very prone to breaking when it's new. My hairline looks horrendous and I don't know what to do.

It's killing my confidence walking around with what looks like a gross hair pom-pom right at my part, especially since I already had to cut about half my hair off to make the ends look thick enough so I don't look like a balding scarecrow. Heeeeelp 😩😭💔
